# FreePads Application Guidelines

## Application Purpose
FreePads is a pads application built with React 19, Vite 7, and Tailwind CSS v4.

## Key Features to Consider
- Pad management and organization
- User interface for creating and editing pads
- Responsive design for various screen sizes
- Modern, clean UI using Tailwind CSS

## Component Architecture
- Create reusable UI components
- Use composition over inheritance
- Implement proper state management
- Consider accessibility (a11y) requirements

## Styling Approach
- Use Tailwind CSS utilities for consistent styling
- Create a design system with reusable components
- Implement responsive design patterns
- Use semantic HTML elements

## State Management
- Start with local component state
- Consider context for shared state
- Use custom hooks for complex state logic
- Plan for future state management needs

## Performance Considerations
- Optimize for fast loading
- Implement lazy loading where appropriate
- Use React.memo for expensive components
- Consider code splitting for larger features